<br>
track record of the other 30ish rotations, in a nutshell:<br>
<br>
kill a mob, get on rotation.<br>
<br>
if you want to try a mob, browse the rotation page, see who's up, and ask them if you can try. (as opposed to fighting for it).<br>
<br>
I mean, really... this is by far the most friendly server ever...<br>
<br>
The only 'conspiracy' that could possibly exist, would be with tradable goods from EP (like tradeskill junk).  Like i said, it is 100% un-monitorable.  I can 3 box earth elemental bows and sell them for 450k plat or whatever the going rate is.. i don't because i consider it a waste of my time.  Anyone who has earth access can do this.  I personally, as GM of my guild don't allow for this to happen, for a myriad of reason, none of which have anything to do with sharing named mobs in the EP...<br>
<br>
Again, like i said 3409022 posts ago, TS stuff is guild by guild handled, i have absolutely no say how FK, TL, NB want to handle thier TS stuff, and none of them have any say what we do with ours.<br>
<br>
Aside from this (which has nothing to do with EP named mobs), what in the world conspiracy could be taking place in the EP forum?<br>
<br>
Its a standard issue rotation, like all rotations: kill mob x, and whallah, you are on the rotation.  The difference is, there is some stuff, namely triggers and such, that get you started to complete events to pop mobs to then kill mobs.  The majority of the people in the EP forums prefer to keep this private, as they are slightly spoiler/jumpstart hints, which cheapens the effort of those involved in killing the mobs.<br>
<br>
That is the ONLY rational reason for keeping it private (that and perhaps the moderator workload - i will not pretend to understand how to set up permissions here).  <br>
<br>
The only rational reason for making it read only (which i personally do not object to, but i am 25% of those who do object) is to keep it from turning into a 450 thread mess, which would deter in the actual forming of the rotation of ~28ish mobs in question, but again it would be spoiling the encounters, against 75% of the parties wishes. (i mean-- threads like this would crop up, on general or rants..)<br>
<br>
The only reason to make it either read only or full access, is to satisfy curiosity, or as rigor puts it, to make us accountable (to making sure we are fair in sharing mobs he knows nothing about <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->     ). <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.drow.org/eq/roster/view.php?Emil" target="top">Emil Sinclair</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, 65th Monk<br>
