<br>
But this isn't ABOUT the server, this is about the RTA FORUMS.  Is it at all possible for you to separate the two?  I'll help you with a few hints:<br>
<br>
1)  In game, you are Emil Sinclair, level 65 monk, bajillion AA, ubah gear, a leader in BoTS, at the top of the food chain with access to zones and content few other people have.  You answer to and are accountable to exactly two entities, your guild and SOE.  There, you get to make the law that everyone has to follow because that is the RTA agreement and you are one of the few who have experience with the content.<br>
<br>
2)  In the RTA, you are Emil Sinclair, ezboard account, representative for BoTS to the RTA.  You answer to 1) your guild, 2) other RTA Representatives, 3) Ezboard.  Here, you are not at the top of the food chain, you are equal in all ways to any other guild representative.  Here, you get to publish the laws you create in game, but you do not get to make the law that the RTA forum exists on except as a guild representative with one vote.<br>
<br>
Most importantly, here you do not get to claim Elemental Planes exception status and make a forum that only you and those like you in the Elemental Planes get to see.  Why?  Because the Elemental Planes don't exist here.<br>
<br>
You can certainly REQUEST a forum, as any RTA Representative supposedly can ...you can even REQUEST it be hidden from the community, as any RTA Representative supposedly can ...but you have REQUESTED nothing ...you demanded, and you received. A demand you have no authority to make.  No one should be allowed to make demands outside the authority of the RTA Representatives.  Having access to the Elemental Planes in the game does not give you that ability here.  Why?  Because, here, you are equal in every way to any other RTA Representative.<br>
<br>
So, let's summarize:  THERE, you are equal to other GMs who have access to the same content you have access to ...HERE, you are equal to any other RTA Representative who has access to the same content you have access to ...the RTA Rep Forum.  That's it.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>The majority of the people in the EP forums prefer to keep this private, as they are slightly spoiler/jumpstart hints, which cheapens the effort of those involved in killing the mobs.<br>
<br>
That is the ONLY rational reason for keeping it private<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I agree, this is the only rational reason.  Is it a good enough reason to claim exemption from the rest of the RTA as a private forum?  Does it truly 'cheapen the effort of those involved' so much so that you can claim immunity from accountability in the RTA, thereby 'cheapening' the authority of the RTA? Or, is it simply an excuse?<br>
<br>
I would argue that the RTA overrides your 'rational reason' simply because any information you may or can provide in that private forum concerning spoilers/jumpstart hints can also be found elsewhere ...freely, if someone were so curious to go find it.  You do not hold the exclusive corner on Elemental Planes information, sorry to say, while the RTA Representatives holds exclusive authority (or should) over the RTA.<br>
<br>
In the end, it's not about your discussions concerning EP rotations ...it's about the discussions you CAN have that don't pertain to EP rotations.  On this matter, you have no rational reason.  You can argue that such discussions simply don't exist ...which would be kind of silly given that one such discussion has already been PROVEN to exist ...but, when push comes to shove, you can't prove such a claim without accountability in place.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>The only rational reason for making it read only (which i personally do not object to, but i am 25% of those who do object) is to keep it from turning into a 450 thread mess, which would deter in the actual forming of the rotation of ~28ish mobs in question, but again it would be spoiling the encounters, against 75% of the parties wishes. (i mean-- threads like this would crop up, on general or rants..)<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->How many 'the only' rational reasons do you have?  First it was &quot;because there are spoilers&quot; ...now it is because &quot;to keep it from turning into a 450 thread mess&quot;.<br>
<br>
Your &quot;turning it into a 450 thread mess&quot; theory is paranoia, plain and simple.  You cannot make an assumption on what MIGHT happen and call it a 'rational reason'.  There is nothing rational about it.<br>
<br>
