<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>You can certainly REQUEST a forum, as any RTA Representative supposedly can ...you can even REQUEST it be hidden from the community, as any RTA Representative supposedly can ...but you have REQUESTED nothing ...you demanded, and you received.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
There was no demand, a few RTA Reps requested of the RTA Admins to create another forum for them, and that request was granted.<br>
<br>
You seem to not understand this, so I will explain it to you.  RTA Administrators are appointed by the RTA Representatives to oversee these forums and by extension the Rotation and Calandar systems hosted on my web server.  Each of us was voted into &quot;office&quot; by a majority vote of the RTA Reps.<br>
<br>
Our duties include, but are not limited to:<br>
- monitoring these forums, and the content within them.  Including making sure posts are in the appropriate location (flames in Flame Central, rotation requests in Rotation Access Requests, etc).<br>
- the creation, formating and organization of forums on the RTA Ez-board site<br>
- granting access to appropriate locations for each guild Rep.  Including the Guild Reps forum, the Rotation/Calendar system.<br>
- mediating in-game disputes, to ensure that the Rotation and Calendar run smoothly.<br>
<br>
So, was the request put forward to all of the RTA Representatives?  No.  Was is still a request? Yes.  A request put forward to the RTA appointed Administrators of this forum.  Which as Administrators of the forum, they have the right to grant.<br>
<br>
You have stated before that you do not trust the Administrators.  However, whether you personally trust the Admins does not matter.  We have been appointed by the RTA Reps to oversee the running of this forum.  The RTA Reps may of course override any dicision that the Admins make, and they may also recall any Admin at any time.  <br>
<br>
