<br>
<br>
1) Hidden forum:  Only rational reason to hide it, is because spoilers will exist in it, that make the posters uncomfortable discussing the rotations with the most optimal accuracy and/or detail.  In effect, opening the forums (blanket, generic opening - either read only, or read/write) would censor the posters who were worried about spoiler info being posted there, as it is not the purpose of the forum - the purpose is to iron out the sharing of mobs, not to be used as a manual to kill (or more specifically, trigger the spawns of some of) these mobs.<br>
<br>
2) Read access to all / Post access to EP: The reasoning behind not wanting this is twofold: firstly, the reason listed above, and secondly - there would in all likelyhood be posts like this created either here, or in rants comenting on rotation mobs. The second reason isnt even really a 'good' reason. I mean who cares if anyone criticized the EP rotation formations? I sure dont! - especially when it can't directly cluter up the forums themselves. However, the spoiler info would be still available, which is still a valid reason to keep them private.<br>
<br>
3) Full acess to all: The reasoning behind not wanting this is the exact same reasoning behind #1, and #2. But this time #2 becomes much more valid, as posting access in the EP forums would lead to pure chaos in there, because it's complicated enough to have 4 guilds, 4 (5 really, earth b) zones, 28ish mobs, varying pop times, etc...It would become chaos if we opened this discussion to thousands(?) of posters.  It would even become chaos if each guild member in the EP had access.  As is stands, ~2 per guild have it (i believe).<br>
<br>
In an ideal world, it would be nice to give read only access to all, where you couldn't even open the threads, but just see a preview of the threads (like when you do a google search, and get a preview of the site).  This would probably be a reasonable compromise for all (i think?).  On the one hand, the EP posters would have a private venue to list their ideas about mobs and so forth, and on the other hand, everyone else would be granted near-total viewing access (making us accountable!!!!!!)  I do not think this is possible with EZ board (though some boards do support it).<br>
<br>
I see your arguments, and personally i even slightly agree with some of the later points, but i also respect the EP posters who do not want to turn the EP area into a &quot;how to get started in the EPs manual&quot;.<br>
