<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>When and where did this happen? <br>
<br>
It didn't<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Prove it, Nyca.  Show me the request.  Who did they ask?  Who granted them their 'request'?  I know who ...you ...the RTA Admins, and I will argue here that you did not and do not, in fact, have the ability to grant such a request.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>One you conviently left out, is he is also an RTA Administrator appointed by the RTA Representatives.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Ah, yes, lets look at the RTA Admins, shall we?<br>
<br>
Vincecross (Founder) (Not really the 'Founder', more like 'most senior', and considers himself 'inactive')<br>
Emil Sinclair (GL BoTS)<br>
Milambus (Noble Blade)<br>
Nyca (Noble Blade?)<br>
Roggulbuk (GL CB)<br>
Sareliel  (inactive, last post was Nov 20, 2000)<br>
TheAdmin (I'm assuming this is a generic account) <br>
Thundaron  (inactive, one post in 5/03, one post in 4/03, last post prior to that was July 13, 2001)<br>
<br>
Once you take away the inactives and the generic account, what are you left with?  You have the majority of the Admins, who made the decision to 'grant' a private elemental planes forum, actually belonging to the 2 of the 4 guilds it would benefit most, BoTS and NB.  Impartial?  Fair?  Hmmm... that question was actually brought up in the nominating of RTA Admins:<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Vincecross as stated in <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11.showMessage?topicID=188.topic" target="top">this thread</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
I would LIKE but its not needed to see 1 rep from the high end, midlevel and guildless/lowend, this isnt necessary or required just a suggestion of fairness so all can see they are being represented.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->...a suggestion of fairness so all can see they are being represented.  Oh well, who the hell cares, it was just a suggestion, right?  During that discussion, our very own Roggulbuk was nominated and appointed ...he was, in fact, the ONLY Admin appointed at that time, even though there were 3 openings available (2 of those open positions are left vacant and inactive).  I have to ask ...where is that suggestion of fair representation?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>There was no demand, a few RTA Reps requested of the RTA Admins to create another forum for them, and that request was granted<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->A 'few' of the RTA Reps 'requested' it of the RTA Admins who 'granted' it, eh?  A 'few' of the RTA Reps (belonging to NB or BoTS) 'requested' it of the RTA Admins (3 of which belong to NB or BoTS, and would benefit) who 'granted' it, eh? ...and how come that request didn't come through the RTA Representatives?  Because you had the right to grant such access?  Vincecross doesn't seem to think so (or didn't at one time): <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Vincecross as posted in <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11.showMessage?topicID=47.topic" target="top">this thread</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> on 3/12/01:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Who makes the rules : YOU DO ((posting entities))<br>
Who Doesnt : ADMINS</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Does the date sound familiar?  It should ...he said it in the same thread that all three of you -Emil, Milambus, and Nyca- were nominated (for the second time) to be Admins.  And, just so we are all clear what ((posting entities)) means: <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>*Posting entity refers to those guilds and alliances that meet the requirements to posts dates on the calendar, and have access to do so.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Does it look familiar, Milambus?  It should ...you said it.  &quot;...meet the requirements to post dates on the calendar, and have access to do so&quot; ...the RTA Representatives, perhaps?  No no, YOU are going to argue that &quot;have access to do so&quot; means &quot;have access to content to do so&quot;.  Certainly there is basis for this, except that when this statement was made, there was only the calendar system and, by having posting access to the calendar, your guild was then a member of the RTA community.  I would have to argue, in this case, that ((posting entities)) were, by definition, all of the RTA Representatives.  It was only later that rotations came along and all of a sudden ((posting entities)) meant something entirely different.  Bottom line is, I truly do believe the original intent (after reading every single post currently in the RTA Rep forum) was to allow the RTA Representatives to govern the RTA, not those who 'have access to content&quot;.  Once you were a member of the commuity, you could help make the rules for the RTA.<br>
<br>
Either way, who DOESN'T make the rules?  ADMINS ...that's right ...gold star for you.<br>
<br>
So, lets skip over to exactly what the Admins CAN DO.  You posted this, Milambus:<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Our duties include, but are not limited to:<br>
- monitoring these forums, and the content within them. Including making sure posts are in the appropriate location (flames in Flame Central, rotation requests in Rotation Access Requests, etc).<br>
- the creation, formating and organization of forums on the RTA Ez-board site<br>
- granting access to appropriate locations for each guild Rep. Including the Guild Reps forum, the Rotation/Calendar system.<br>
- mediating in-game disputes, to ensure that the Rotation and Calendar run smoothly.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
...and here's what Vincecross said are the duties of the Admin in <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11.showMessage?topicID=36.topic" target="top">this thread</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> on 3/9/01:<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Heh I am thinking some guilds think this is a power thing. Let me give you the reality of the admin life. No choice is made without either email/tell or posting in the admin section. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>We have no real power there is nothing we do besides place Give new access to the calenda, answer questions, get yelled out by the n00b posting guilds/alliances because they dont understand or havent read, get personal attacks from time to time (these are rare), rearrange calendar dates and the rare sanction against a guild</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.'<br>
<br>
Simple majority rules. Sometimes choices are made without ALL the admins but always with atleast 3 (2/3 of current admins) and I have yet seen an admin make a choice and not have all the other admins agree. We are fair and level headed, you may see some of the brighter colors of us when we get attacked but who wouldnt in those situations.<br>
<br>
Trust me when I say there is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>nothing to be gained by being an admin other then helping keep and established well intentioned idea alive</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.<br>
<br>
I really hope this clears it up to the people nominated and for the people who think this is some kind of power. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
... and again in <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11.showMessage?topicID=47.topic" target="top">this thread</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> on 3/12/01:<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>What do admins do you ask?<br>
Well for one if every admin was from the same guild it would mean nothing for the fact remains <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>nothing is decided by them except for sanctunes</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, Wich at this point is 1 month and any remaining posting days first offense 2nd is 2 months, we havent gone further because no on has gotten to the second level.<br>
Admins job here is a headache, they try to streamline the posts for change to the calendar, they summorize the info much like you would summurize a book.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>They announce punishment that ALL admins vote on.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
Usualy its pretty cut and dry weather a guild deserves a break or not (so far no one has been given a break) the only reason there is a vote so as to ensure that the choices made are not biased in any way. <br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>There is no POWER in being a admin, so get that thought out of your head</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. All it is , is someone volunteering there time to deal with YOU (and trust me dealing with YOU is a pain sometimes)<br>
As far as Thun and me go we will still be here and out votes will count but our main purpose is to take care of the actual Board and web pages, and the overall calendar mainanence, and offer our experience to the new admins who get to look evil like I seem to have my last few days :&gt<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
If you still feel absolute that we cant have 2 MFH <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>then call a vote and see what the community wants</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->If anything, you are given judiciary authority to decide on, and present, sanctions that are levied against guilds that have been found in violation of the RTA law and janitor duty.  That is it.<br>
<br>
I'm sorry ...did Vincecross say you have the ability to GRANT (as in decide who gets access to what) to people who have no right to access other than the fact that you say so, or did he say you have the ability to GIVE access (as in forum maintenance and pushing the right button) to people who have already earned that access by meeting RTA requirements?  What do YOU think he meant? <br>
<br>
I don't believe you get to decide whether or not a forum should exist in private exclusion of the RTA ...the RTA representatives would have that responsibility ...by majority vote ...which, I'm surprised to find, actually occured here at one time (not too much of that has happened since you 3 signed on though ...funny).  Of course, you should know that, Emil, Milambus, and Nyca ...because you've been here as Admins for a long time.  In March of 2001, this would never have been allowed.  You KNOW it would have gone to RTA Representative vote ...you know it, and I know it.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>So, was the request put forward to all of the RTA Representatives? No. Was is still a request? Yes. A request put forward to the RTA appointed Administrators of this forum. Which as Administrators of the forum, they have the right to grant.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Yes, it is true, you are appointed administrators of this forum.  Unfortunately, no where ...and I mean no where I have been able to find ...does that appointment give you the right or the ability to act as representatives for the RTA Representatives in matters of RTA law.  There is simply no written precedence for this leap of judgement.  Your abilities, as near as I can determine from 'the original intent' that is actually WRITTEN anywhere, you are a judicial committee and a janitorial service.  Anything else you are making up as you go along.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>You have stated before that you do not trust the Administrators. However, whether you personally trust the Admins does not matter. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I never said I do not trust the Admins.  I said I don't trust YOU, there's a big difference.  I think all of you ...Emil, Nyca, and Milambus ...have broken the golden Admin commandment in this case and overstepped your 'authority' by making a decision that wasn't yours to make to the benefit of your respective guilds.  I have provided endless debate on the conflict of interest reflected here.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>We have been appointed by the RTA Reps to oversee the running of this forum. The RTA Reps may of course override any dicision that the Admins make, and they may also recall any Admin at any time.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->You have been appointed as janitors and as, supposedly, fair and impartial judges with the authority to dispense punishment to those guilds who break the rules of the RTA.  The RTA Reps should never have to 'override' any decision the Admins make because, simply, the Admins do not have any decision making power outside of judiciary punishment.<br>
<br>
But, this is where we find ourselves now.  You made a decision that was not yours to make, and I get to be stuck with debating with you for e-fargin-ternity on how wrong you really are.  You asked me a few pages back what happens if I could not rally enough RTA Representative support behind my argument that no one will even take this issue for vote to the Representative forum.  As Milambus, of Noble Blade, I would expect that you would want this discussion to die here, in General chat, rather than take it to the RTA Rep forum where you would have the mere possibility of losing your precious forum.  As Milambus, RTA Admin, judiciary committee member, mediator, I would think it would be your DUTY to carry this REQUEST for a fair vote to the RTA Rep forum as a supposedly impartial official.<br>
<br>
Problem is, the three of you are superb ventriloquists ...sound is coming our of your RTA Admin mouth ...but you are talking out your NB / BoTS ass.  You simply cannot defend an 'authority' you never had in the first place. <p><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->These are stupid ideas and these people should be given a damn good thrashing with a clue stick.<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.clanbashemded.org" target="top"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.clanbashemded.org/images/rigsig.gif" style="border:0;height:150;width:300;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=438887" target="top"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:white;font-family:verdana;font-size:x-small;">Magelo Profile</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showMessageRange?topicID=932.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showMessageRange?topicID=932.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showMessageRange?topicID=932.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showMessageRange?topicID=932.topic&start=61&stop=80>4</a><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showMessageRange?topicID=932.topic&start=81&stop=100>5</a><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showMessageRange?topicID=932.topic&start=101&stop=120>6</a><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showMessageRang